Put chicken breasts, onion, garlic, yam, and stock in a casserole; cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes; remove and save chicken pieces. Strain stock through a sieve; return strained stock to casserole. Add chicken, scallions, cilantro, potatoes, corn, and capers to stock; simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Remove from heat; discard scallions and cilantro sprigs. Add yogurt, stir over low heat for 1 minute. Serve in deep soup bowls accompanied by avocado.